{
  "_readme": [
    "Hand-curated ingredient -> USDA SR Legacy mapping. NEVER auto-matched: naive matching gave",
    "'salmon fillet' -> 'Vegetarian fillets' and 'eggs' -> 'Eggs, scrambled, frozen mixture'.",
    "",
    "'q' is a USDA-style description used to resolve an fdc_id; the resolver records the chosen",
    "fdc_id + description so every nutrient value is traceable. 'id' pins an fdc_id explicitly.",
    "State matters: recipes say '70 g dry' (rice, quinoa, pasta) and '150 g cooked' (lentils),",
    "so the mapping must pick the matching USDA state or calories will be off by ~3x.",
    "'negligible': spices/sauces used in tsp amounts - still mapped, never silently zeroed."
  ],
